<i>noun</i>: 직책 [직책], 직업 [지겁], 직무 [징무], 직 [직], 일자리 [일ː짜리], 일거리 [일ː꺼리], 일감 [일ː깜], 업 [업], 밥벌이 [밥뻐리], 밥그릇 [밥끄륻], 밥거리 [밥꺼리], 노릇 [노륻] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>직책 [직책]</dt><br>
<dd>duty; job</dd><br>
<dd>직업상 맡은 일에 따른 책임.</dd><br>
<dd>Responsibilities given to a person based on his/her job or position.</dd><br>
<dt>직업 [지겁]</dt><br>
<dd>occupation; job</dd><br>
<dd>보수를 받으면서 일정하게 하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A regular activity done in exchange for payment.</dd><br>
<dt>직무 [징무]</dt><br>
<dd>duty; job</dd><br>
<dd>직업상 맡은 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A task that one is in charge of based on one's job or position.</dd><br>
<dt>직 [직]</dt><br>
<dd>1. office</dd><br>
<dd>공무원 등이 국가로부터 받은 일정한 직무나 직책.</dd><br>
<dd>A duty or position given to a civil servant, etc., by the government.</dd><br>
<dd>2. job; occupation</dd><br>
<dd>생계를 위하여 일정한 기간 동안 계속하여 하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A regular activity done for a specific period of time for one's living.</dd><br>
<dd>3. position</dd><br>
<dd>맡은 직위나 직무.</dd><br>
<dd>One's post or duty.</dd><br>
<dd>4. employment</dd><br>
<dd>직업이나 직위를 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A word used to mean an occupation or position.</dd><br>
<dt>일자리 [일ː짜리]</dt><br>
<dd>job</dd><br>
<dd>일터나 직장과 같이 직업으로 삼아 일하는 곳.</dd><br>
<dd>An occupation or a place where one is employed like a workplace, an office, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>일거리 [일ː꺼리]</dt><br>
<dd>1. job</dd><br>
<dd>일해서 돈을 벌 수 있는 거리.</dd><br>
<dd>A piece of work that enables one to earn money.</dd><br>
<dd>2. work to do; task</dd><br>
<dd>의무적으로 해야 하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A piece of work that one should do.</dd><br>
<dt>일감 [일ː깜]</dt><br>
<dd>1. piece of work; job</dd><br>
<dd>일해서 돈을 벌 수 있는 거리.</dd><br>
<dd>Work that one can do to earn money.</dd><br>
<dd>2. materials</dd><br>
<dd>일을 할 때 필요한 재료.</dd><br>
<dd>Materials needed when working.</dd><br>
<dt>업 [업]</dt><br>
<dd>1. occupation; job</dd><br>
<dd>보수를 받으면서 일정하게 하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>Work that one does regularly for pay.</dd><br>
<dd>2. duty</dd><br>
<dd>책임을 가지고 꼭 해야 할 중대한 일이나 임무.</dd><br>
<dd>Important work or mission that one should do or perform with responsibility.</dd><br>
<dd>3. karma</dd><br>
<dd>불교에서, 미래의 좋고 나쁨을 결정한다고 하는 현재의 행동.</dd><br>
<dd>In Buddhism, one's current actions that are believed to affect one's fortune in the future.</dd><br>
<dt>밥벌이 [밥뻐리]</dt><br>
<dd>1. job</dd><br>
<dd>먹고살기 위하여 하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>Something that one does in order to make one's living.</dd><br>
<dd>2. living</dd><br>
<dd>겨우 밥만 먹고 살 수 있을 만큼의 벌이.</dd><br>
<dd>Earnings just enough to make a living.</dd><br>
<dt>밥그릇 [밥끄륻]</dt><br>
<dd>1. rice bowl</dd><br>
<dd>밥을 담는 그릇.</dd><br>
<dd>A bowl for holding rice.</dd><br>
<dd>2. job; work</dd><br>
<dd>(속된 말로) 밥벌이를 위한 일자리.</dd><br>
<dd>(slang) A job for making a living.</dd><br>
<dt>밥거리 [밥꺼리]</dt><br>
<dd>1. ingredients for rice</dd><br>
<dd>밥을 지을 재료.</dd><br>
<dd>The ingredients for cooking rice.</dd><br>
<dd>2. job; work</dd><br>
<dd>먹고살기 위하여 하는 일거리.</dd><br>
<dd>Things to do for to make a living.</dd><br>
<dt>노릇 [노륻]</dt><br>
<dd>1. job; work</dd><br>
<dd>(낮잡아 이르는 말로) 직업으로 하는 일이나 직책을 맡아 하는 역할.</dd><br>
<dd>(disparaging) What one does as his/her occupation; or a role assumed in line with his/her position.</dd><br>
<dd>2. role; part</dd><br>
<dd>역할에 어울리는 행동이나 태도.</dd><br>
<dd>Behavior or attitude that suits one's role.</dd><br>
<dd>3. situation; circumstances</dd><br>
<dd>일의 상황 또는 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>The situation or circumstances in which things are happening.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>